attributes.comment: Patients have the right to clear and accurate knowledge about the sex of their chosen providers. Many women (adult human females) prefer to be seen by women providers when dealing with sensitive health issues. However men in dresses identify, they are still males. Any proposal that would obfuscate the true sex of the provider is harmful to women. When will this administration stop bowing down to a gender ideology that is neither based in science nor commonly accepted by average Americans?
